DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH
 BUSINESS ANALYST
 (PAY BAND 5)
 OPEN
 FREDERICTON
 The Department of Health is seeking an individual to join the Francophone Affairs, Acute Care and Decision Support Division as a business analyst in Fredericton.
 As a member of the Health Analytics team, the successful candidate will report to the Manager of Health Information Management and Data Warehouse and will be responsible for activities associated with the effective identification and delivery of solutions to meet the business needs of multiple client departments. Your responsibilities will include but are not limited to:

 Be familiar with and follow the GNB Solutions Delivery Framework, standards and practices;
 Facilitate workshops with technical and business colleagues to capture and document requirements, processes, future state etc.;
 Work with technical and business teams to analyze business needs to design or procure solutions that address business requirements;
 Work with technical and business teams to define and document solution benefits, and outcomes;
 Participate in the creation, review and update of other deliverables, including but not limited to:

 Reporting requirements;
 Business impact analysis;
 Business process diagrams;
 Use cases / business models;
 Gap analysis;
 Testing & Implementation plans.

 Leading teams of solutions specialists, programmers, Database Administrators, and business stakeholders in coding, testing and implementing functionality that is identified by any of the aforementioned deliverables;
 Maintain strong and collaborative relationships with Business Application Services Team Members, Project Managers, Enterprise Architecture and other SNB teams;
 Maintain strong and collaborative relationships with client departments and business owners;
 Participate in activities related to the procurement of goods and services in accordance with the Procurement Act, including but not limited to:

 Creating RFPs and RFIs for medium and large procurement efforts;
 Developing scorable criteria;
 Developing evaluation criteria for submissions;

 Taking part in evaluation committees for reviewing and scoring submissions.

 ESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS: The successful candidate must possess a Bachelor's degree in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Economics, Computer Science, Business Administration, Engineering or a related area and a minimum of five (5) years of recent experience as a Business Analyst in an IT related field.
 An equivalent combination of education, training and experience may be considered.
 Written and spoken competence in English and French is required. Please state your language capability.
 Applicants must clearly demonstrate the essential qualifications to be given further consideration. Please ensure that preferred language for assessment is identified on your resume.
 In the event that this competition poses difficulties in recruiting a qualified candidate, a covering off appointment at a lower level may be made. In that case, candidates with less than the required related years of experience may also be considered.
 ASSET QUALIFICATIONS: Preference may be given to candidates that possess one or more of the following asset qualifications:

 Recognized professional business analysis certification such as PMI-PBA, IIBA-CBAP;
 Experience with Microsoft Power BI;
 Experience working with large data sets.

 Subject to the response to this competition, candidates may be required to demonstrate on their application one or more of the asset qualifications in addition to the essential qualifications in order to be given further consideration.
 BEHAVIOURAL COMPETENCIES: The successful candidate will possess the following behavioural competencies:

 Effective Interactive Communication;
 Analytical Thinking / Judgement;
 Relationship/Network Building

 TECHNICAL COMPETENCIES: The successful candidate will possess the following technical competencies:

 Written Communication;
 Planning and Organization Skills;
 Knowledge of Conflict Management Practices;
 Presentation Skills;
 Specialized Subject Matter Expertise and Knowledge.

 Salary: $60,606 to $84,656 per annum
 We encourage applicants to apply on-line at https://www.ere.gnb.ca/competition.aspx?lang=E&t=Y or by mail at the following address by July 19, 2022 indicating competition number 35-22-0025. This competition may be used to fill future vacancies at the same level.
 Department of Health
