 The purpose of the role 

 Under the responsibility of the Inventory Control Manager, the incumbent of this role will be responsible for analyzing and verifying the integrity of the data entered into the various systems as well as ensuring compliance with procedures and process compliance by all stakeholders in relation with stores inventories. 

 Job description 



Ensure that all stores inventory processes are followed in our ERP system;
Analyze, explain inventory discrepancies between systems and make the necessary follow-ups and corrections;
Follow up on the various movements of store inventories, realize appropriate analyses, and make corrections if necessary;
Make sure every store inventory procedures are carefully followed by all stakeholders;
Actively participate in the coordination of inventory process in stores, with internal resources or with a third party (cycle, annual or any other count);
Analyze and explain the various discrepancies as a result of physical inventory in stores and ensure the integrity of store inventories in the ERP for annual, cycle or any other necessary count;
Produce various inventory and movement reports for the monthly reconciliation at end of fiscal month;
Works closely with various internal stakeholders regarding situations/issues related to inventories or processes;
Seize opportunities to optimize processes to increase process efficiency;
Collaborates in the development or improvement of operational procedures and participates in their implementation;
Participate in the execution of various tests at the ERP level;
Perform all other related tasks to support the Manager and the team
